title: The Owl and the Pussycat
subject: librivox; audiobook; literature; poetry
description: Librivox's weekly poetry project for the week of January 22, 2006: The Owl and the Pussycat, by Edward Lear. Librivox's weekly poetry project for the week of January 22, 2006: The Owl and the Pussycat is a famous nonsense poem by Edward Lear, first published in 1871. Its most notable historical feature is the introduction of the runcible spoon.
